---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Banking Solutions | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Comprehensive guide to banking options for Maine cannabis businesses. Discover cannabis-friendly banks, credit unions, and financial strategies for your dispensary."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1501167786227-4cba60f6d58f?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Banking Solutions</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-banking-solutions/">banking</a> for your Maine cannabis business</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Fueling Your Vision" type="success">
      Securing a banking partner is a huge milestone that turns your dream into a high-speed engine. While it takes some effort, finding that right local credit union or bank that "gets" your passion makes everything feel real. It's the moment your business truly gains its wings.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Banking remains one of the biggest challenges for cannabis businesses. While state-legal, cannabis remains illegal at the federal level, causing many traditional banks to avoid the industry. However, options exist for Maine operators.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Banking Challenge</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Federal prohibition creates risk for banks</li>
        <li>Many banks refuse cannabis businesses</li>
        <li>Account closures can happen suddenly</li>
        <li>Limited access to credit</li>
        <li>Cash-heavy operations create security risks</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cannabis-Friendly Banks</h2>
      <p>Several institutions serve Maine cannabis businesses:</p>
      
      <h3>Credit Unions:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Some Maine credit unions serve cannabis businesses</li>
        <li>Often more flexible than large banks</li>
        <li>Check local options</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>State-Chartered Banks:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Some state banks are more willing</li>
        <li>Build relationships early</li>
        <li>Document everything</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>SAFE Banking Act</h2>
      <p>The Secure and Fair Enforcement (SAFE) Banking Act would protect banks serving cannabis businesses. While not yet federal law:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provides safe harbor for financial institutions</li>
        <li>Would reduce cash-only operations</li>
        <li>Monitor for updates</li>
        <li>May pass in future sessions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cash Management</h2>
      <p>Until full banking access, manage cash carefully:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Secure safes and vaults</li>
        <li>Armored car services for deposits</li>
        <li>Cash management policies</li>
        <li>Employee training on cash handling</li>
        <li>Limit cash on premises</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Practices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Start banking relationships early</li>
        <li>Be transparent about your business</li>
        <li>Maintain excellent records</li>
        <li>Build relationships with multiple institutions</li>
        <li>Plan for account closure scenarios</li>
        <li>Consider payment processing solutions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Banking options exist but require research</li>
        <li>Credit unions may be more flexible</li>
        <li>Cash management is critical</li>
        <li>Build relationships before you need them</li>
        <li>Monitor SAFE Banking Act developments</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="external-resources">
      <h2>Further Reading & Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Cannabis regulations are subject to change; always consult with the Maine Office of Cannabis Policy and qualified legal counsel.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .external-resources { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .external-resources ul { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
  .external-resources li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
</style>
